cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the problem of predicting the effect of physical interactions with objects in the environment, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a method that combines analytical and learned models, which involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper uses sensory input to predict physical interactions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper deals with optimal action selection, which is a problem in artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with physical interactions, which is a problem in control systems, suggesting that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
